Twenty-three states will receive
almost $300 million in federal payments for enrolling children
from low-income families in public health programs, the U.S.
said.  A 2009 federal law allows states to qualify for the money
if they surpass enrollment targets for Medicaid, the federal-
state health program for the poor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
